The '''Abyssal walker''' is one of many monsters which can be found in the [[Abyss]], and also in the [[Abyssal Area]] ([[fairy ring]] code: {{fairycode|ALR}}). They are difficult to hunt as they seem to have a high [[defence]], [[hitpoints]], and [[strength]], although they have low accuracy. It should also be noted that they are difficult to [[poison]], although they are not immune to it. Abyssal walkers killed in the Abyss yield much lower [[experience]]. These monsters are [[aggressive]], but will stop being aggressive after a while as well as the [[Abyssal guardian]] and the [[Abyssal leech]].

If hunting Abyssal monsters for [[essence pouch]]es, it is recommended to use magic against these, as despite their high magic defence, they have a very low magic level, enabling magic spells to hit accurately. At relatively high Defence and [[Magic]] levels (70+) a player should have little to no trouble with them, even accounting for the aggressive monsters in the outer ring of the Abyss. Alternatively, a [[crush weapon]] or a weapon with a secondary crush style can be used effectively due to their low crush defence.

